Such sweet music.

1739
01:44:31,265 --> 01:44:34,132
- Stand back.
- Silence that harpsichord!

1740
01:44:34,351 --> 01:44:36,342
MAESTRO CADENZA: What? Uh-oh!
GARDEROBE: Maestro!

1741
01:44:36,479 --> 01:44:37,765
Darling! At last!

1742
01:44:37,897 --> 01:44:39,854
I'm coming, my love.

1743
01:44:40,024 --> 01:44:41,890
This is it!

1744
01:44:42,026 --> 01:44:45,109
The fat lady is singing.

1745
01:44:45,863 --> 01:44:48,025
(VOCALIZING)

1746
01:44:48,240 --> 01:44:49,321
(ALL SHOUTING)

1747
01:44:49,909 --> 01:44:51,195
<i>Bravissima!</i>

1748
01:44:54,830 --> 01:44:56,412
(ALL GROANING)

1749
01:44:56,707 --> 01:44:58,744
LUMIÈRE: (LAUGHS)
Watch your toes!

1750
01:44:58,876 --> 01:44:59,876
(ALL SCREAMING)

1751
01:45:00,377 --> 01:45:01,959
(LUMIÈRE LAUGHING)

1752
01:45:02,213 --> 01:45:04,500
LUMIÈRE: That's it! Go! Go!

1753
01:45:04,715 --> 01:45:07,082
- (VOCALIZING AND GIGGLING)
- LUMIÈRE: <i>Bon voyage.</i>

1754
01:45:07,343 --> 01:45:08,833
(ALL SCREAMING)

1755
01:45:11,847 --> 01:45:13,463
Safe trip home.

1756
01:45:13,557 --> 01:45:15,173
And stay out!

1757
01:45:15,684 --> 01:45:18,517
(ALL CLAMORING)

1758
01:45:20,272 --> 01:45:22,183
(MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

1759
01:45:35,454 --> 01:45:36,910
Hello, beast.

1760
01:45:40,209 --> 01:45:41,791
I'm Gaston.

1761
01:45:42,545 --> 01:45:44,286
Belle sent me.

1762
01:45:46,882 --> 01:45:49,249
Are you in love with her?

1763
01:45:51,095 --> 01:45:53,928
Did you honestly think
she'd want you?

1764
01:45:56,058 --> 01:45:57,093
(GROWLS)

1765
01:45:59,645 --> 01:46:00,976
(GROWLING)

1766
01:46:09,864 --> 01:46:10,945
Belle!

1767
01:46:12,616 --> 01:46:14,402
Where is he?

1768
01:46:14,577 --> 01:46:15,942
When we return to the village...

1769
01:46:16,078 --> 01:46:17,660
you will marry me.

1770
01:46:17,830 --> 01:46:19,537
And that beast's head...

1771
01:46:19,623 --> 01:46:21,580
